## Project Overview

The **CCU_nano** project aims to enhance the efficiency and safety of cooling devices by providing real-time monitoring and control. By analyzing temperature and power consumption metrics, 
the system can make informed decisions to activate or deactivate the cooling load, ensuring optimal performance and energy savings.

## Features

- **Comprehensive Monitoring**: Tracks device temperature, voltage, current, power consumption, and ambient room conditions.
- **User-Friendly Interface**: CYD display with EEZ Studio-designed UI for real-time data visualization and user interaction.
- **Automated Control**: Relay mechanism triggers based on user-defined thresholds for temperature and power consumption.
- **Data Logging**: Records historical data for analysis and troubleshooting.
- **Modular Design**: Easily adaptable to various cooling devices and environments.

## System Architecture

The system comprises the following components:

- **Sensors**:
  - Temperature sensor for the cooling device.
  - Voltage and current sensors to monitor power consumption.
  - Ambient temperature and humidity sensor for room conditions.
- **Microcontroller**: ESP32 for processing sensor data and controlling the relay.
- **Display**: CYD screen with UI developed in EEZ Studio.
- **Relay Module**: Controls the power supply to the cooling device based on sensor inputs and user-defined thresholds.

